# MSYS2 MinGW64 Build Default

When a build/compile request is made for this repository, use PowerShell with MSYS2 MinGW64 by default.

Use this exact command:

```powershell
$env:MSYSTEM="MINGW64"; & "C:\msys64\usr\bin\bash.exe" -lc "cd '/c/Users/LLU2HC/Documents/Long-Stuff/HCMUT/computer_engineering_project/Autosar_SecOC' && mkdir -p build && cd build && cmake -G 'MinGW Makefiles' .. && mingw32-make -j4"
```

Guidelines:
- Do not replace this with `rebuild_pqc.sh` unless the user explicitly asks.
- Keep the `& "C:\msys64\usr\bin\bash.exe"` call operator form.
- Use forward-slash MSYS path inside bash (`/c/Users/...`).
